annotation.TEXT: And down here, I can get a star coin. (I guess that's what I'm collecting in this hack instead of Yoshi coins.)
Okay, I'm thinking this block might have a feather, so as soon as I deal with these duders, I'm going to try to clone this block.
Umm... Did I not have running speed there?
Argh! Stupid ninja turtle... Which one of the TMNT was it that wore the yellow bands? Michelangelo? No, wait, he wore orange, right? Then, who wore yellow?

Unfortunately, this means that I can't choose 2 players and alternate between Marina and Luica (like how I alternated between Reimu and Sanae in Hakurei Adventure Mission). Although, if there's a way to switch characters mid-game, let me know!
Goal tape average so far: 110 / 3 = 36.667 stars each.
Hmm... I guess not. Oh, well. Let's keep going.
Aww... Just another coin... And the block looks sad now. Also, for some reason, I can't climb this vine.
And, I get another 40, and I also get my reserve feather back, as a reward for babysitting the P-switch for so long!
Aw, no! This hack has disabled cape flight! Well... I'd better keep this in mind for the future...
Yep, I've seen that kind of block in hacks before. And up here, I get another 1-Heart-P!
Ooh, coins... And there's also this ? block on a vine... Maybe it's a power up?
Okay, this looks like a setup for a 1-up combo, so let's do it right!
Umm... I think I left that room too soon. Let's go back in.
Man, there sure are a lot of shell-less blue koopas that are out for my blood!
Ooh. Tricky.
Yep. So, what was with the vine inside the starting house earlier?
Hey there, hidden 1-up. How's it going?
mebamme's translation: "Ma & Lu" (probably stands for Marina and Luica)
Okay, game. I'll take those pillow feathers now.
Oh, also, any help in identifying music would be greatly appreciated too! ...Whoa, I can move fast on the world map! Wheeee!!!
That startled me. Maybe I should've followed the arrow, but whatever.
Die, you evil ninja turtle! (You can't be a good ninja turtle, since none of the TMNT even wear yellow!)
Oh, yeah, and this is a Japanese hack, of course, so if anyone wants to translate some of this, feel free to do so! (I'm guessing world 1 is called "Cabbage Woods".)
Oh, man. Is this going to be a remake of SMB's 1-1? Well, maybe not. It's not entirely accurate.
Ah, I can go down this pipe!
So, yeah. It looks like the Groovy level had a few modifications to it, but still used the original demo's actions. Okay, let's get started now.
And there's the goal! Okay, big money, big money, big money... No whammies, no whammies...
No custom music here?
And that's every star coin from this level.
Oh, man. A cape in just the second level? Does this game want to be broken so early?
Ooh, red coins. Also, those clouds sure are thin.
Huh. There's hidden blocks here. For a split-second, I was thinking I might need to do some springboard trickery to get up there.
And now for world 1-1. (I would assume this is Cabbage Woods 1, but correct me if I'm wrong.)
Okay, let's start with this house here...
To be continued...
So, which one of these two levels should I play next? 1-3, or 1-A? Place your votes now, and we'll find out where I'll go next time!
And now I race on over to 1-2, which is a red level, so I've gotta find two exits there, obviously. (Um... I don't think these levels are all simply called "Cabbage Woods"...)
Even the midpoint, the springboard, coins, and ? blocks have different graphics.
And, yep. That was indeed the other exit I needed, which leads to 1-3. I'm assuming that'll be a water level.
Whoa! Well, that's an interesting way to enter the bonus game!
I can climb this vine, right?
...STOP! Well, I got a 40 plus another 1♥P, so I guess that's good.
...Super Marina World! This hack was requested to me by Jolpenman, and I decided I'd try it out.
Ooh, fragile-looking blocks. I bet I know how they'll behave...
Oh, well. Let's get out of here.
Hello everyone, and welcome to...
No, it doesn't look like I needed the P-switch to get across there.
Okay, midpoint gets me embiggened, so that's a start.
That was kind of interesting.
Hmm... I wonder what that sign there says... Well, let's enter the house.
That seemed risky.
And these ? blocks contain a flower and a feather, which is cool.
And with all 5 star coins collected, I get another 1♥P!
I wonder why these levels don't all have custom music...
Yay! I got a 1-Heart-P!
Hi... shell?! What the? Doesn't that block normally have a Yoshi? Looks like the title demo's been altered a bit, so let's watch.
BGM: Tetris Attack - Yoshi's Theme
I see Chucks are no different than usual. They even have their usual graphics, unlike the koopas and power ups.
So, is it safe for me to assume that that was the secret exit?
Oh, my god. Okay, seriously. I've got to stop getting smacked around by these duders!
BGM: Super Mario Advance 4: SMB3 (GBA) - World-e (The e-reader area)
It's another goal! Bah. I only got a 30 this time, but that's still enough for a bonus game.
I can still make that silly spin jump sound effect, though!
Whoa, holy crap!
Hmm... Maybe I should've sped some of this footage up...
And now, what's to the right of this pipe?
Huzzah! Too bad I can't do my victory dive bombs...

Marina and Luica? Huh... Well, I did some testing off screen after I finished making this video, and it appears that this isn't a "number of players" choice. Whoever you choose here is who you play as for the whole game, and it's still single player.
Although, maybe it's a loose remake. So, I'd expect to be able to go down that pipe, and there to be a hidden 1-up just to the right of it...
Hmm... A P-switch, but do I truly need it?
Toasty! Aww... I guess fried enemies don't become coins in this hack. To be honest, I think I prefer my fried foes to become money, but whatever.
"1-A"? Yep, that must've been the secret exit. But whether it was or not, I'd of course want to head back to 1-2 for the exit that I didn't get yet.
Wow, it's like the game wants to stuff me with more feathers than a pillow!
Whoop, didn't quite hit the platform there.
I think I'll keep my reserve flower for now.
That's an interesting setup just before the goal here.
Wait, I gotta check every pipe!
Luigifan22222's translation: "...? The castle which I have not looked at in such a place! I will go... World 1 Cabbage Woods"
No Banzai Bill this time? Oh, I think it's because of the shell I brought in that's now occupying sprite slot 0, which is the only slot that Banzai Bills can occupy.
Bah. I failed the block cloning attempt, but the block did indeed have a feather.
